          "attrs": {},
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Land Pollution."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " Do ONE of the following and discuss with your counselor:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "12607",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "In an area (yard, park, golf course, farm, etc.) approved by your counselor, make a list of the pesticides, herbicides, and fertilizers used and how often they are applied. Identify the benefits of their use and the environmental impact, including effects on non-target species (including humans), what happens if the chemicals infiltrate into the groundwater, and what happens to any runoff of the chemicals."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Do We Really Need Pesticides? (video)",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GLllZ-qiXJA"
            },
            {
              "title": "Bald Eagle Study (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/1eXj6QKjw_o?si=oppPQY9SRxO1a7Ne"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "12608",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Learn about the erosion process and identify an example of where erosion occurs. Determine where the eroded material ends up and how erosion can be minimized."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Soil Erosion | Causes, Effects, and Solutions (video)",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BoSUEIkK_Y4"
            },
            {
              "title": "How Was the Grand Canyon Formed? (video)",
